                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9411/134</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Press Release Issued by the Department of State on April 14,
                        1941</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1941-04-14">April 14, 1941</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>In reply to inquiries at his press conference today, the Secretary of State made
                    the following statement: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The significance of the pact between the Soviet Union and Japan relating
                            to neutrality, as reported in the press today, could be overestimated.
                            The agreement would seem to be descriptive of a situation which has in
                            effect existed between the two countries for some time past. It
                            therefore comes as no surprise, although there has existed doubt whether
                            the two Governments would or would not agree to say it in writing. The
                            policy of this Government, of course, remains unchanged.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
